A warm, golden-lit airport lounge interior in Studio Ghibli style, featuring a weary traveler with a small suitcase being guided by a kind airport worker in uniform who gestures welcomingly toward plush seating areas. The scene captures a moment of unexpected hospitality, with soft afternoon light streaming through large windows showing planes on the tarmac. The lounge has cozy details like steaming teacups on side tables and comfortable armchairs. In the background, subtle construction scaffolding is visible through the windows, hinting at renovation. The color palette is warm amber and soft cream tones, with the gentle, hand-painted texture characteristic of animated films. The expressions on both figures convey genuine human connection—gratitude meeting generosity.
